HEADWORD: Crusta
<hw>Crus"ta</hw> <pr>(kr?s"t?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., shell,
crust, inlaid work.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A crust or shell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A gem engraved, or a plate embossed in low relief,
for inlaying a vase or other object.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crustacea</ent>⟦br⟧
